        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(model-fallback): classify Codex usage-limit payloads",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes a model fallback gap where Codex usage-limit error payloads could be treated as a completed embedded-agent result instead of advancing to the next configured fallback model.\n\n## Root Cause\n\n`classifyEmbeddedAgentRunResultForModelFallback()` already inspects embedded error payload text and calls `classifyFailoverReason()`. The shared matcher classifies usage-limit text as `rate_limit`, but `classifyBusinessDenialErrorPayloadReason()` only allowed `auth`, `auth_permanent`, and `billing`.\n\n## What Changed\n\n- Allows `rate_limit` as a fallback-safe embedded error-payload classification.\n- Adds focused regression coverage for the Codex usage-limit payload.\n- Keeps scope limited to embedded result classification.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior tested: a Codex usage-limit payload should classify as `rate_limit` with code `embedded_error_payload`, instead of returning `null`.\n\nReal environment: local OpenClaw checkout using production `classifyEmbeddedAgentRunResultForModelFallback()`.\n\n### Before patch, upstream/main\n\nCommand:\n\n`EXPECT_RATE_LIMIT=0 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/__tmp_codex_usage_limit_real_proof.test.ts`\n\nObserved terminal output:\n\n```text\n[test] starting test/vitest/vitest.agents.config.ts\n\n RUN  v4.1.8 /home/rev/projects/openclaw\n\nstdout | src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/__tmp_codex_usage_limit_real_proof.test.ts > Codex usage-limit fallback real behavior proof > classifies the real Codex subscription usage-limit payload shape\ncodex_usage_limit_classification=null\n\n ✓  agents  src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/__tmp_codex_usage_limit_real_proof.test.ts (1 test) 93ms\n\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  1 passed (1)\n   Start at  15:28:01\n   Duration  1.09s (transform 936ms, setup 401ms, import 449ms, tests 93ms, environment 0ms)\n\n[test] passed 1 Vitest shard in 6.56s\n```\n\n### After patch\n\nCommand:\n\n`EXPECT_RATE_LIMIT=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/__tmp_codex_usage_limit_real_proof.test.ts`\n\nObserved terminal output:\n\n```text\n[test] starting test/vitest/vitest.agents.config.ts\n\n RUN  v4.1.8 /home/rev/projects/openclaw\n\nstdout | src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/__tmp_codex_usage_limit_real_proof.test.ts > Codex usage-limit fallback real behavior proof > classifies the real Codex subscription usage-limit payload shape\ncodex_usage_limit_classification={\"message\":\"openai/gpt-5.5 ended with a provider error: You've reached your Codex subscription usage limit. Next reset in 32 minutes, Jun 20 at 3:44 PM EDT. Wait until the reset time, use another Codex account if available, or switch to another configured model/provider.\",\"reason\":\"rate_limit\",\"code\":\"embedded_error_payload\",\"rawError\":\"You've reached your Codex subscription usage limit. Next reset in 32 minutes, Jun 20 at 3:44 PM EDT. Wait until the reset time, use another Codex account if available, or switch to another configured model/provider.\"}\n\n ✓  agents  src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/__tmp_codex_usage_limit_real_proof.test.ts (1 test) 40ms\n\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  1 passed (1)\n   Start at  15:28:37\n   Duration  506ms (transform 238ms, setup 162ms, import 183ms, tests 40ms, environment 0ms)\n\n[test] passed 1 Vitest shard in 5.77s\n```\n\n### Focused validation\n\nCommands:\n\n`node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/result-fallback-classifier.test.ts src/agents/model-fallback.test.ts`\n\n`git diff --check`\n\nObserved terminal output:\n\n```text\n[test] starting test/vitest/vitest.unit-fast.config.ts\n\n RUN  v4.1.8 /home/rev/projects/openclaw\n\n ✓  unit-fast  src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/result-fallback-classifier.test.ts (12 tests) 13ms\n\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  12 passed (12)\n   Start at  15:29:18\n   Duration  419ms (transform 161ms, setup 0ms, import 302ms, tests 13ms, environment 0ms)\n\n[test] starting test/vitest/vitest.agents.config.ts\n\n RUN  v4.1.8 /home/rev/projects/openclaw\n\n ✓  agents  src/agents/model-fallback.test.ts (81 tests) 4928ms\n\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  81 passed (81)\n   Start at  15:29:21\n   Duration  7.08s (transform 895ms, setup 174ms, import 1.86s, tests 4.93s, environment 0ms)\n\n[test] passed 2 Vitest shards in 16.10s\n```\n\n`git diff --check` passed with no output.\n\n## What was not tested\n\nI did not force a live Codex account into a usage-limit state. That would be flaky and account-state dependent. This proof exercises the deterministic fallback classification boundary using the production embedded result classifier.\n\nA separate follow-up may still be needed if Codex emits this same banner as normal assistant text before it becomes an `isError` payload.\n\n## Tests\n\nAI-assisted: yes.",
